Reformatted Question: Howe resupplied in Nova Scotia and headed for New York City with the British fleet, as it was considered the key to securing the continent. How many more Patriots were casualties than British in the New York and New Jersey campaign?

Answer: According to the passage, <fact1>1,500 Patriot casualties</fact1> were inflicted, and <fact2>the British suffered 400 casualties</fact2>. <fact1>1,500</fact1> - <fact2>400</fact2> = 1,100. So the answer is {1,100}.

Reformatted Question: In January 1918, Romanian forces established control over Bessarabia as the Russian Army abandoned the province. Although a treaty was signed by the Romanian and Bolshevik Russian governments following talks between 5 and 9 March 1918 on the withdrawal of Romanian forces from Bessarabia within two months, on 27 March 1918 Romania formally attached Bessarabia to its territory, based on a resolution passed by the local assembly of that territory on its unification with Romania. Romania officially made peace with the Central Powers by signing the Treaty of Bucharest on 7 May 1918. Under the treaty, Romania was obliged to end the war with the Central Powers and make small territorial concessions to Austria-Hungary, ceding control of some passes in the Carpathian Mountains, and to grant oil concessions to Germany. In exchange, the Central Powers recognised the sovereignty of Romania over Bessarabia. The treaty was renounced in October 1918 by the Alexandru Marghiloman government, and Romania nominally re-entered the war on 10 November 1918. The next day, the Treaty of Bucharest was nullified by the terms of the Armistice of Compiègne. Total Romanian deaths from <fact1>1914</fact1> to <fact2>1918</fact2>, military and civilian, within contemporary borders, were estimated at 748,000. How many years passed while 748,000 Romanians died?
Answer: According to the passage, the deaths occurred from <fact1>1914</fact1> to <fact2>1918</fact2>. <fact2>1918</fact2> - <fact1>1914</fact1> = 4. So the answer is {4}.

Answer: According to the passage, <fact1>Dermontti Dawson made the Pro Bowl for the third consecutive year</fact1>. So the answer is {3}.

How many more Thai visitors did Bangkok have in 2010 compared to other foreign visitors?

Answer: According to the passage, <fact1>there were 26,861,095 Thai visitors</fact1> and <fact2>11,361,808 foreign visitors</fact2> in 2010. To find the difference, we need to subtract the number of foreign visitors from the number of Thai visitors: <fact1>26,861,095</fact1> - <fact2>11,361,808</fact2> = 15,499,287. So the answer is {15,499,287}.

Reformatted Question: Armenia gave way to communist power in late 1920. The Soviet 11th Red Army's <fact1>invasion of the First Republic of Armenia started on the 29th of November 1920</fact1>. The actual transfer of power took place on December 2 in Yerevan, when the Armenian leadership approved an ultimatum presented to it by the Soviet plenipotentiary Boris Legran. Armenia agreed to join the Soviet sphere, while Soviet Russia agreed to protect its remaining territory from the advancing Turkish army. The Soviets also pledged to take steps to rebuild the army, to protect the Armenians and not to persecute non-communists, although the final condition of this pledge was reneged when the Dashnaks were forced out of the country. The Soviet Government proposed the annexation of the Nagorno-Karabagh and Syunik regions of Armenia to Soviet Azerbaijan. This step was strongly rejected by Garegin Nzhdeh, who declared <fact2>Syunik as a self-governing region on December 25, 1920</fact2>. In January 1921 Drastamat Kanayan sent a telegram to Njdeh, suggesting allowing the sovietisation of Syunik, through which they could gain the support of the Bolshevik government in solving the problems of the Armenian lands. Njdeh again proved himself as a long-sighted politician, he did not depart from Syunik and continued his struggle against the Red Army and Soviet Azerbaijan. How many days passed from when the invasion of the First Republic of Armenia started to when Syunik was declared as a self-governing region?

Answer: According to the passage, <fact1>the invasion of the First Republic of Armenia started on the 29th of November 1920</fact1> and <fact2>Syunik was declared as a self-governing region on December 25, 1920</fact2>. To find the number of days, we need to calculate the difference between these two dates. November has 30 days, so from November 29 to November 30 is 1 day. December has 25 days from December 1 to December 25. Therefore, the total number of days is 1 + 25 = 26. So the answer is {26}.

Reformatted Question: From <fact1>November 1943</fact1>, during the seven-week Battle of Changde, the Chinese forced Japan to fight a costly war of attrition, while awaiting Allied relief. The following Soviet offensive was halted on the pre-war Estonian border by the German Army Group North aided by Estonians hoping to re-establish national independence. This delay slowed subsequent Soviet operations in the Baltic Sea region. By late May 1944, the Soviets had liberated Crimea, largely expelled Axis forces from Ukraine, and made incursions into Romania, which were repulsed by the Axis troops. The Allied offensives in Italy had succeeded and, at the expense of allowing several German divisions to retreat, on 4 June, Rome was captured. The Allies had mixed success in mainland Asia. In March 1944, the Japanese launched the first of two invasions, an operation against British positions in Assam, India, and soon besieged Commonwealth positions at Imphal and Kohima. By June, the Japanese had conquered the province of Henan and begun a new attack on Changsha in the Hunan province. How many months passed between the Battle of Changde and the Allied attack in Italy?

Answer: According to the passage, the Battle of Changde started in <fact1>November 1943</fact1> and the Allied attack in Italy occurred in <fact2>January 1944</fact2>. <fact2>January 1944</fact2> - <fact1>November 1943</fact1> = 2 months. So the answer is {2}.

Answer: According to the passage, <fact1>47.9% of births were to unmarried women</fact1> in 2015. To find the percentage of births to married women, we subtract this percentage from 100%. 100% - <fact1>47.9%</fact1> = 52.1%. So the answer is {52.1}.

Mindon had deployed a larger, well-equipped army. The Siamese forces again reached Kengtung but could not break through. The Siamese forces withdrew to the border in May 1855. How many did it fail to dislodge the Burmese from?

Answer: According to the passage, it failed to dislodge the Burmese from <fact1>2 places (Kengtung and Sipsongpanna)</fact1>. So the answer is {2}.
